Formatting & Structure Requirements

Code Style

Use consistent indentation (2 spaces for JavaScript/JSON, standard for HTML)

Include complete function signatures with JSDoc annotations

Group related helpers/utilities near their consumers or in clearly named sections

Write all helper functions completely‚Äîno stubs or references to "similar code above"

Documentation

Place explanatory text outside code blocks

Place actual code inside fenced markdown blocks with language tags

Include inline comments for complex logic

Add JSDoc for all public functions

Security

Do not embed secrets or API keys

Use Script Properties service for sensitive data

Demonstrate usage via clearly marked placeholders (e.g., SCRIPT_PROPERTY_KEY="<set in Script Properties>")

Include setup instructions for required properties

File Interdependencies

If files reference each other, include brief comments noting the relationship

Example: // Called by saveData() button click in HTML UI

Example: // Calls processData() from code.gs backend

