Understanding Google Apps Script Triggers

Trigger Fundamentals

What are Triggers? Triggers are automated mechanisms that execute your functions in response to specific events or time conditions. Think of them as "event listeners" that watch for changes and automatically run your code when something happens.

Types of Triggers: Simple vs Installable

Simple Triggers

Simple triggers are built-in, easy-to-use functions that run automatically based on specific events.

Characteristics:

No setup required - just name your function correctly

Limited permissions and capabilities

Cannot access services requiring authorization

Have strict time limits (30 seconds for most)

Cannot trigger other installable triggers

Available Simple Triggers:

