What Was Wrong: The error "ReferenceError: myFunction is not defined" means JavaScript couldn't find a function with that exact name when trying to execute your code. This happens when:

Name Mismatch: You defined myfunction() (lowercase) but called myFunction() (uppercase F). JavaScript is case-sensitive!

Scope Issue: The function was defined inside another function, making it inaccessible from outside that "parent" function.

Syntax Error: A syntax error earlier in your script prevented the entire file from loading, so your function never got defined.

