Global Scope: Define functions at the "top level" (not inside other functions) so they're accessible everywhere

Clean Syntax: Make sure every opening bracket ( has a closing ), and every opening brace { has a closing }

Why This Approach:

JavaScript requires exact name matches (case-sensitive)

Functions need to be in the right scope to be callable

Syntax errors can prevent the entire script from loading

Testing each function separately helps identify which one has issues

